Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Delay", "::", "usage"}], "=", 
   "\"\<Delay[\[Tau]] specifies an interval of fixed duration \[Tau] without \
any radio-frequency fields. \nDelay[\[Tau], evgen] species an interval of \
fixed duration \[Tau] with an additional evolution generator applied to the \
spin system. The evgen argument may be a Hamiltonian operator, a relaxation \
superoperator, or one of the Function, PeriodicFunction or \
PeriodicGeneratorFunction arguments used to specify a time-dependent \
evolution generator.\nDelay[Automatic] and Delay[Automatic, evgen] define \
flexible delays which are automatically adjusted so that the enclosing \
PulseSequence has the specified duration. If the PulseSequence contains \
several Delay[Automatic..] objects, the syntax PulseSequence[{.. \
Delay[{Automatic,x1}..]..Delay[{Automatic,x2}..]..}..] adjusts the delays so \
as to maintain the specified ratio between the x-parameters. For example, \
PulseSequence[\[Tau],{Delay[{Automatic,1}],Delay[{Automatic,2}]}] generates \
PulseSequence[\[Tau],{Delay[\[Tau]/3],Delay[2\[Tau]/3]}].\nExpand may be \
applied to a Delay object, in order to convert it into an explicit event.  \n\
\>\""}], ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.683110930825906*^9, 3.683110960429503*^9}, {
   3.683957681054821*^9, 3.683957681056888*^9}, {3.68473148634813*^9, 
   3.6847319047868156`*^9}, {3.684732038249943*^9, 3.68473207538481*^9}, {
   3.691833458137909*^9, 3.691833470340055*^9}, {3.691833563553875*^9, 
