Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"ShapedPulse", "::", "usage"}], "=", 
   "\"\<ShapedPulse[spins,\[Tau]p,{\[Tau],{amplitude,phase,frequency}},\
options] specifies a continuously shaped radiofrequency pulse of duration \
\[Tau]p applied to spins spins. The amplitude, phase and frequency arguments \
are arbitrary functions of \[Tau], with the origin of the local time variable \
\[Tau] being in the centre of the pulse, by default (for other options, see \
below). The amplitude argument specifies the nutation frequency for the \
selected spins as a function of \[Tau]. The phase argument specifies the \
phase of the radiofrequency field in the rotating frame. The frequency \
argument specifies the frequency offset of the shaped radiofrequency field. \n\
If the spins argument is missing, all spins in the current spin system are \
assumed. \nIf the frequency argument is missing, zero frequency offset is \
assumed. If the phase argument is also missing, zero phase is assumed. \nThe \
syntax ShapedPulse[spins,\[Tau]p,{\[Tau],amplitude},options] assumes an \
amplitude-modulated rf field as a function of local time variable \[Tau]. For \
example, ShapedPulse[spins,\[Tau]p,{\[Tau],\[Omega]nutmax Cos[\[Omega]mod \
t]}] specifies a cosine-modulated pulse with maximum nutation frequency \
\[Omega]nutmax and modulation frequency \[Omega]mod.\nSyntax of the form \
ShapedPulse[spins,\[Tau]p,{{\[Tau],x}, {amplitude,phase,frequency}},options] \
indicates that the local time variable \[Tau] has a time origin located at a \
point which is a fraction x of the pulse duration from the start of the \
pulse. A value of x=0 indicates a time origin at the beginning of the pulse; \
a value of x=1 indicates a time origin at the end of the pulse. The default \
is x=1/2 (time origin at the centre of the pulse).  \nThe options may contain \
rules for AmplitudeFactor and PhaseShift. AmplitudeFactor is used to specify \
the rf field amplitude relative to a nominal value, allowing simulation of \
the effect of rf inhomogeneity. For example AmplitudeFactor\[Rule]0.9 \
indicates a rf field amplitude which is 10% less than the nominal value. The \
PhaseShift\[Rule]\[CapitalPhi] option may be used to impose a constant phase \
shift \[CapitalPhi] on the pulse shape. Both of these options may be passed \
down from the enclosing PulseSequence object.\nExpand may be applied to a \
ShapedPulse object, in order to convert it into an explicit event.\>\""}], 
  ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.683110930825906*^9, 3.683110960429503*^9}, {
  3.683957681054821*^9, 3.683957681056888*^9}, {3.68473148634813*^9, 
